descr: "A formal computable definition of a graph of resources - that is, a coherent set of resources that form a graph by following references. The Graph Definition resource defines a set and makes rules about the set."

fields.name: resourceType
fields.descr: "This is a GraphDefinition resource"

fields.name: url
fields.descr: "An absolute URI that is used to identify this graph definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or an instance. This SHALL be a URL, SHOULD be globally unique, and SHOULD be an address at which this graph definition is (or will be) published. The URL SHOULD include the major version of the graph definition. For more information see [Technical and Business Versions](resource.html#versions)."

fields.name: _url
fields.descr: "Extensions for url"

fields.name: version
fields.descr: "The identifier that is used to identify this version of the graph definition when it is referenced in a specification, model, design or instance. This is an arbitrary value managed by the graph definition author and is not expected to be globally unique. For example, it might be a timestamp (e.g. yyyymmdd) if a managed version is not available. There is also no expectation that versions can be placed in a lexicographical sequence."

fields.name: _version
fields.descr: "Extensions for version"

fields.name: name
fields.descr: "A natural language name identifying the graph definition. This name should be usable as an identifier for the module by machine processing applications such as code generation."

fields.name: _name
fields.descr: "Extensions for name"

fields.name: status
fields.descr: "The status of this graph definition. Enables tracking the life-cycle of the content."

fields.name: _status
fields.descr: "Extensions for status"

fields.name: experimental
fields.descr: "A boolean value to indicate that this graph definition is authored for testing purposes (or education/evaluation/marketing), and is not intended to be used for genuine usage."

fields.name: _experimental
fields.descr: "Extensions for experimental"

fields.name: date
fields.descr: "The date  (and optionally time) when the graph definition was published. The date must change if and when the business version changes and it must change if the status code changes. In addition, it should change when the substantive content of the graph definition changes."

fields.name: _date
fields.descr: "Extensions for date"

fields.name: publisher
fields.descr: "The name of the individual or organization that published the graph definition."

fields.name: _publisher
fields.descr: "Extensions for publisher"

fields.name: contact
fields.descr: "Contact details to assist a user in finding and communicating with the publisher."

fields.name: description
fields.descr: "A free text natural language description of the graph definition from a consumer's perspective."

fields.name: _description
fields.descr: "Extensions for description"

fields.name: useContext
fields.descr: "The content was developed with a focus and intent of supporting the contexts that are listed. These terms may be used to assist with indexing and searching for appropriate graph definition instances."

fields.name: jurisdiction
fields.descr: "A legal or geographic region in which the graph definition is intended to be used."

fields.name: purpose
fields.descr: "Explaination of why this graph definition is needed and why it has been designed as it has."

fields.name: _purpose
fields.descr: "Extensions for purpose"

fields.name: start
fields.descr: "The type of FHIR resource at which instances of this graph start."

fields.name: _start
fields.descr: "Extensions for start"

fields.name: profile
fields.descr: "The profile that describes the use of the base resource."

fields.name: _profile
fields.descr: "Extensions for profile"

fields.name: link
fields.descr: "Links this graph makes rules about."
